      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You've hit on a very real and important point regarding the bias inherent in corporate hiring language. Focusing too heavily on vague concepts like \"polish\" and \"predictability\" absolutely risks reinforcing a narrow, often white-centric definition of professionalism. These markers frequently correlate with specific socioeconomic backgrounds, which unfortunately leads to hiring homogeneity. A more objective evaluation would focus on measurable skills, such as demonstrated problem-solving under pressure, rather than the aesthetic packaging of the candidate.",
